@node intro "Introduction"

Yaan-chat is based on an old chatter I wrote called Kewl-Chat...  The name
was changed cos some 13 year old kid decided to release a totally differant
modem chatter called Kewl-Chat (SPIT!), and it got mentioned in the mags etc
so I just changed this prog :)

Anyway, here's the intro :)

This is the ultimate chat door for the MAX's Professional BBS system.  It 
was originally written for MAX's BBS v1.54 using Ari Tsironis's AMOS
extension, but it was slow and had no support for paragon so I wrote the
Kewl-Doors extension which is nice and fast :), this DOES support MAX's 
v1.54 in a way, check the installation section for more info!

The program itself is designed to be a replacement for MaxsChat by Edward
Lawford and has a lot more features that I have thought of to help Sysops
and users who are always chatting...

Various versions of this chatter have been used on my BBS for over 15 months
now, so I *KNOW* it's pretty stable :)))))))))))))))))

It also has nice features like raw download support, button banks + much 
more!

@endnode
@node sysreq "System Requirements"

You'll need MAX's BBS Professional or MAX's BBS v1.54 as a start :)

You'll also need a decent spec miggy :(

This eats under 10% CPU time on my 28Mhz 030 miggy, so any machine with an 
020 or greater should be fine :)

If you don't use MAX's Pro, then you MUST be running the 16bit version of
MAX's v1.54, otherwise the door will crash!

@endnode
@node inst "Installation & Configs"

The easy bit :^)... Just use the following:-

	Lha X YaanChat.Lha Doors:
	
This will work for any system that has Doors: assigned to where the BBS has
it's doors..

The archive has the following files.
	
    YaanChat (dir)
	YaanChat	- The main proggy :)
	YaanChat.Cfg	- The configuration file.
	Hydracomm	- The hydracom support file.

This program also needs the reqtools library to work.
Do NOT change the names of any of these files or the directory name!


Configuration File Explained
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

The YaanChat.cfg file is a straight ascii file, you can use virtually any
text editor to change it :)

The supplied example is as follows:-

Downloads:KC_Downloads/
BTW
by the way
BTW:
By the way,
AFAIK
as far as I know
IYSWIM
if you see what I mean?
ATM
at the mo
ROTFL
heheheheh..  Rolling on the floor laffing :) hehehehhe
FN
BTW: do you want to join Fluffy Net??????
#
#


Line 1 - This is where you want Yaan-Chat to place any files sent to you
	 during a chat...  This is used by the Raw Upload function.
Line 2+  These are the auto inserts to be used by Yaan-chat :)))))))))
	 They simply have the abbreviation on 1 line, and the expanded text
	 on the following line...   If you've never seen these in action 
	 before, then just typing BTW in the chat, the BTW will be deleted
	 and will type `by the way' for you :))))..  These are recursive!!!
	 So you can have inserts within inserts!  (Look at the last one for
	 an example)....  Be careful tho!  If an insert loops into another
	 insert then the machine will just keep typing it until you reset :(
	 Inserts are only expanded when you press the space key after the
	 word!
	 
	 Use 2 lines of #'s to terminate the list :)

Auto-inserts can also have control codes in them, use these to control the
Yaan-chat text options :)

As this door uses MAX's Pro, it grabs any other info it needs (Like screen 
address, serial device, sysop name etc etc) from the MAX's exe in ram :)


Running
~~~~~~~

This is where it gets complex!!!!

Execution under MAX's Pro v1 - v1.66
In the menu editor set.

Key:   Function:  Extra:    Lo Acc:    Hi Acc:	  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 /       34	    0 	     10000	10000	  Doors:YaanChat/YaanChat +

Remember the +!!!!  It starts it as a MAX's Pro door :))))


Execution under MAX's Pro v1.70+
This is the same as Mpro 1.66 for a stand alone chat..  If you also have
Kewl Page 2.3+ (By Steve Clack) installed you can use...

Key:   Function:  Extra:    Lo Acc:    Hi Acc:	  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 C	  43        0          1        10000     YaanPage.text
 
This runs the door list YaanPage.text, and if the sysop clicks answer when
a user pages, it automatically runs Yaan-Chat!!!!!
(A door list is very similiar to the IntroDoor.text file, just a 
customisable name :)))))))  Only available in MAX's Pro v1.70!)


Execution under MAX's BBS v1.54

This is where the hektic part starts...  Yaan-Chat has always been purely
available for MAX's Pro, so getting it to run under MAX's, it starts its
own door port emulator..  This will ONLY work on the 16bit version of MAX's
v1.54!!!!!!!!!!!!

Key:   Function:  Extra:    Lo Acc:    Hi Acc:	  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 /       34	    0 	     10000	10000	  Doors:YaanChat/YaanChat

I can't garantee it'll work, but if it works the first time you try it, 
it'll continue to work :)))))

The 16bit version of MAX's v1.54 is 245096 bytes long...

@endnode

@node inuse "Using Yaan-Chat when started :))))))"

Button Bank Window
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Keep this window active while typing!   Yaan-Chat takes the sysop input
from it to avoid key loss!!!

This window is semi-seperate from the main code, all it does is add key
presses to the sysop text buffer.  The effect is like a normal window tho :)

You can type into this window even during file xfers!!!  When the xfer is
finished, the buffered chars just get dumped into the chatter :)))))))


Other Control Codes
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

This is where the fun starts :)).  Options marked SYSOP are Sysop only...
Funny that!

Ctrl L	- Clear Your Screen
Ctrl K	- Clear Both Screens

Ctrl F	- Freeze The Users Time Remaining	(SYSOP)
Ctrl R	- Resume The Time Counter	(SYSOP)

Ctrl Q	- Quit.  Requires Sysop Access (5000+)
Ctrl Z	- Zap Off.  Quick Logoff	(SYSOP)

Ctrl D	- Raw Download :)))))	(SYSOP)
Ctrl X	- Raw Upload ;-)	(SYSOP)

Ctrl E  - Writing mode select :)	(SYSOP)
HELP    - Brings up the online help window :)))))	(SYSOP)

Cursor Keys  -  Moves the cursor around the chat window! :)))	(SYSOP)



Those Options Explained
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Screen Clears
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Ctrl-L is the standard screen clear command, like in MAXs Chat.
Ctrl-K clears both screens.  Useful if chatting on a new subject or chatting
       on a dodgy subject when someone walks in the room...


Time Freezing
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

This stops the minutes going down for the user :)))
It's useful because users can be a little pissed off when you chat to them
and after the chat, they only have 2-3 minutes left!!


Quitting
~~~~~~~~

Please note that it is Ctrl-Q to quit and not escape!!  The main problem with
MAXs Chat was that the cursor keys and a few others could also quit the main
chat program.  There is only 1 Ctrl-Q!
Another problem, was that if you imported a piece of ansi text, the first 
escape code would quit the program and the rest could mess up the BBS :((

Ctrl-Z does a quick logoff.  It does not twit the user.


Raw Downloads
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

A first for a chat program???
Firstly, a file requester will appear.  This is a multi select one so you can
send as many files in one go as you want :)))

Then a ANSI menu will appear so the user can select the xfer method :)

MAX's Transfer - The files will be sent 1 at a time like normal.
Hydra Transfer - The workbench screen will flip to the front and 4 windows
		 will be opened.  The top 2 are transfer status and the other
		 2 are for the hydra chat mode :).  Press Right Amiga - C
		 to break in for a chat.
		 Press Escape to quit transfer/After transfer has ended.
Smodem Transfer - Virtually the same as Hydra really..  Just uses the Smodem 
		  Program instead.

Abort Transfer - Do I need to explain this?

** IMPORTANT: If your user is running MUI-Hydracom, then tell them to run
that before you select files to send!  They will then see Yaan-Chat running
in a window :))
		 
You must have Hydracom & Smodem in your Yaanchat directory for these options
to work, otherwise you're just limited to Z-modem...
		 
		 
Raw Uploads
~~~~~~~~~~~

You will be asked if transfer for the transfer method.  The actual transfer 
is the same as raw download.

All uploads go to your directory set in the YaanChat config :)


Writing Modes
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

There are 4 differant styles of writing supported by Yaan-Chat...

Normal	- normal text :)  (Bit obvious!)
Elite   - el!7e  (Best I can do in ascii)..  That funny looking text you
	  see on elite/warez boards that you can't ever read :)
Tagged  - whErE thE vOwEls ArE cApAtAlIsEd lIkE thIs :)))
Johnathon Ross - This weplaces all R's with w's :)))
	  e.g.  People of jewusalam...  Wome is youw fwiend!
	  

Cursor Keys
~~~~~~~~~~~

Just wack the cursor keys to move the cursor around like in a text editor :)
useful to go over mistakes or                all
			      type      this     the
				   like              time :)


I think that's about it now :)))))))))))))

(Read the credz & greetz :))) )


